{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> σχεδ-όν</b>, <br /> <i>adverb</i>, (ἔχω, σχεῖν): <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> of Place, <b>near, hard by</b>, <i>Epic dialect</i> and Lyric poetry, δυσμενέες δ᾽ ἄνδρες σ. εἵαται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.100; σ. εἴσιδε γαῖαν 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 5.392, compare 24.493 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; σ. οὔτασε <b>at close quarters</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.458; μή πώς σ᾽ ἠὲ βάλῃ ἠὲ σ. ἄορι τύψῃ 20.378, compare 13.576, 16.828: sometimes with _dative_, οὐ γάρ σφιν παῖδες σ. εἵαται 10.422; νῆσοι ναιετάουσι σ. ἀλλήλῃσι 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.23; οἳ δή σφι σ. εἰσι 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Scutum Herculis” 113 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; so στάθεν τύμβῳ σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 10.66 (also πὰρ ποδὶ σ. [prev. author] “O.” 1.74 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀμφ᾽ ἀνδριάντι σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “P.” 5.40): more frequently with _genitive_, Φαιήκων γαίης σ. 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 5.288, compare 475, 6.125, 9.117, 10.156, etc.; σ. αἵματος 11.142. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> with Verbs of motion, σ. ἐλθεῖν τινι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.304, compare 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Scutum Herculis” 435 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τινος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.439; Ἀχαιίδος 11.481; ὅστις σ. ἔγχεος ἔλθῃ 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 20.363. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i> ofrelationship, καὶ πηῷ περ ἐόντι μάλα σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.441. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>similar to</b>, with <i>dative</i>, σ. τούτοις.. αἱ παραλλαγαὶ.. εἰσίν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Iamblichus Philosophus “de communi mathematica scientia” 27. \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> of Time, [θάνατος] δή τοις. εἶσι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 17.202, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.284; σοὶ δὲ γάμος σ. ἐστιν 6.27 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; σοὶ.. φημὶ σ. ἔμμεναι, ὁππότε.. [the time] is <b>near</b>, when.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 13.817. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> after [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], <b>about, approximately, more or less, roughly speaking</b>, σ. κατὰ ταὐτά [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.42; σ. τι ταὐτά 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Parmenides” 128b; σ. τι τοιαῦτα [prev. author] “Smp.” 201e; σ. τι ταῦτα [prev. author] “Grg.” 472c; σ. πάντες 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.65, 2.48, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 6.5.33, cf. NT.Act.13.44, “PRyl.” 81.7 (2nd c.AD)\">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]; πάντα σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 350b21; σ. ἅπαντας 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 1157; πάντες σ. ἢ οἵ γε πλεῖστοι 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “Epicteti Dissertationes” 1.11.7; σ. ἐκ κρηνῶν οἱ πλεῖστοι ῥέουσιν 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 350b34; σ. περὶ τριακόσια στάδια [prev. work] 351a14 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σ. τι πρόσθεν ἢ.. <b>not long</b> before, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 736; σ. ἤδη τῆς κοίτης ὥρη προσέρχεται ὑμῖν 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.20 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σὺν τοῖς θεοῖς σ. ἔσται ὁ διάλογος (audit) ἕως τῆς λ τοῦ Παχών [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PTeb.” 58.58 (2nd c.BC)\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; σ... τὸν αὐτὸν.. καιρόν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Inscription Prien.” 105.13 (1st c.BC)\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; also σ. ἴσως [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Sophista” 253c, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Topica” 118a13; σ. που 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 36.10; σ. ὡς εἰπεῖν 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Analytica Posteriora” 79a20, “Rh.” 1382b28, 1st c.BC: Geminus Astronomicus 16.28 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σ. εἰπεῖν one might <b>almost</b> say, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Sophista” 237c, 2nd c.BC: Athenaeus Mechanicus 3.4, “POxy.” 1033.11 (4th c.AD), “PLips.” 34.16 (4th c.AD). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__IV.2</b></Level3> with Verbs (frequently in <i>perfect</i>), especially of saying or knowing, σ. εἴρηχ᾽ ἂ νομίζω συμφέρειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 3.36; εἴρηται σ. ἱκανῶς 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Analytica Priora” 32a16 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; διώρισται σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Pol.” 1328a19; τὸν ἐμὸν.. σ. ἤδη νομίζων ἐκτετοξεῦσθαι βίον 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 33; σ. ἐπίσταμαι 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 43; σ. οἶδα 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 898; ἐγὼ σ. τὸ πρᾶγμα γιγνώσκειν δοκῶ 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 860 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; frequently used to soften a positive assertion with a sense of modesty, sometimes of irony, σ. γὰρ.. συνίημι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.19 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σ. τι τὴν σὴν οὐ καταισχύνω φύσιν <b>I dare say</b> I do not.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 609 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σ. τι μώρῳ μωρίαν ὀφλισκάνω <b>I dare say</b> it is a fool who thinks me foolish, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ant.” 470 \">Refs</a>]; σ. δέ τι καὶ τὸ ξύμπαν <b>generally speaking</b> in every respect, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.68 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σ. οὐδ᾽ ὁπωστιοῦν σοι πείσεται <b>probably</b> not at all, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 61c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σ. γὰρ ἔχω ὃ εἰπὼν ἀναγκάσω σε <b>I think</b> I have an argument, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Phdr.” 236d. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__IV.3</b></Level3> used in affirmative answers, <b>I suppose so, I dare say</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Sph.” 250c, 255c, +others \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> <b>perhaps</b>, ὑποδραμὼν σ. φασεῖ (φάσει codices) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Dius cited in 5th c.AD: Stobaeus, Joannes 4.21.17. \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__VI</b></Level2> ={σχέδην}, ἠκολούθει σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Bellum Judaicum” 1.17.2 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>] (unless = followed <b>at no long distance</b>).","strongNumber":"G4975","accentedUnicode":"σχεδόν","shortDef":"nearly, almost","mediumDef":"<i>primarily</i> <b>near,</b> of place; hence, <b>nearly, almost,</b> <ref='Act.13.44'>Acts 13:44;</ref> 19:26; <ref='Heb.9.22'>Heb. 9:22</ref>*","stepGloss":"nearly","stepTransliteration":"schedon","count":3,"_es_Definition":"adv. casi, por poco","_zh_tw_Definition":"非常接近, 幾乎, 只差一點點","_zh_Definition":"非常接近, 几乎, 只差一点点","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"hầu như; hầu hết; gần hết","_zh_tw_Gloss":"幾乎","_es_Gloss":"casi","_zh_Gloss":"几乎"}]}